2. Metrices

    Assumption:

        -> New link created daily = 10M
        -> (100: 1 ratio) = 1000M (read redirects) approx 1B

    i. Write

        QPS = 10000000 / (24 * 3600) = 115 QPS (normal time)

        peak time = 115 * 3 = 350 QPS

    ii. Read

        QPS = 1000000000 / (24 * 3600) = 11500 QPS (normal time)

        peak time = 11500 * 3 = 35000 QPS


    iii. Storage

        Short code = 7 character = 7 bytes
        Long Url = 200 character = 200 bytes
        UserId = UUID = 36 bytes
        TimeStamp, Metadata = 50 bytes
    ---------------------------------------------
        Total               = 300 bytes

    
    Url Per day = 10M / day  * 365 days = 3.65 billion URLs / per year
    Storage per year = 3.65 billion * 300 bytes = 1.1 TB / year

    5 - year storage = 5 * 1.1 TB = 5.5 TB


    ** Short Code Lenght

        Use base62 encoding (a-z, A-Z, 0-9) (base62 because base64 uses characters which are not url friendly)

        6 charachter = 62^6 possible combinations = 56.8 billion unique codes
        7 charachter = 62^7 possible combinations = 3.5 trillion unique codes



